    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-03-31T12:29:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-03-31T12:29:00-05:00" n="152"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d152">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.61321/8</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FDR1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Francis</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Vologda</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-03-31T20:00:00+02:31">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 31, 1918, 8 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received April 1, 8.18 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>50. I have received Consul General’s March 30, noon, cable to you and endorse
                        <persName corresp="#p_HEL1">Harris</persName> appointment as Consul General,
                    Siberia, reporting <persName corresp="#p_SM1">Summers</persName> and myself. I
                    approve Consul General’s request to purchase cotton, provided arrangements made
                    for transporting same from Moscow to safety in event Moscow captured. <persName
                        corresp="#p_HEL1">Harris</persName> is <persName corresp="#p_SJF1"
                        >Stevens</persName>’s representative on commission mentioned in my No. 44.
                    Consul General coming to Vologda on 5th for a conference.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_FDR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Francis</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
